S, and lends perspective to the debate about where to steer the CES in the years ahead. Contributors outline how the CES project began and how far it has come, assess the quantity and types of data that have been collected, and explore the theoretical and methodological developments that have been involved. Looking toward the future, the book highlights the challenges that lie ahead and provides suggestions for change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aElectionsxResearchzCanada. 0aElectionszCanadaxHistory. 0aVoting researchzCanada. 0aVotingzCanadaxHistory. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / Campaigns & Elections.2bisacsh1 aBilodeau, Antoine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBilodeau, Antoine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBlais, André, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBélanger, Éric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClarke, Harold D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGidengil, Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnston, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKanji, Mebs, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKanji, Mebs, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKay, Barry J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKornberg, Allan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeduc, Lawrence, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeisel, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNadeau, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPammett, Jon H., econtr